 where his mob went.<br>
<br>
If you go on the assessment, that your always going to get aggro, and act accordingly, you're never caught off guard.<br>
<br>
Arcane Rune changes everything! Once you get it, never unmem it.. 1500hp with no component. In Valor, that means about 5 seconds of safety after you get aggro. If the MA can't pull aggro off you in 5 seconds, then I'd rethink my life expectancy in that group.  As soon as the MA gets aggro back, recast AR and then slow. <br>
<br>
As a caster, the best thing you can do for yourself is get a horse (or lizard) you don't sit to med so you don't generate hate. <br>
<br>
Take a few mins before you start hunting, and talk to your group, ask the MA what he's using for weapons to generate hate and if he's worked with enc's before, ask him what his &quot;comfort zone&quot; is.. alot of tanks already know that they can hold aggro after a certain amount of damage has been done, and they can often give you good insight into when to cast. <br>
<br>
Don't put yourself on the line with every pull! If the MA can't hold stand up to an unslowed mob for a few seconds to generate hate, then you have a problem.  IMO SK's are the best at getting immediate hate, I rarely get aggro from tashing/slowing when a good SK is at the helm. On the other side, I almost always get aggro from a warrior, but warrior tanks SHOULD have the Hp's/AC to take the hits so you can hold off a bit.<br>
<br>
I generally hold  with 96% as a general guideline, by then any tank should have sufficient aggro to allow you to start casting. <p>May the moonlight shine gently upon you;<br>
