<br>
This tactic works well IF you can get them mezzed and KEEP them mezzed long enough to get everything off. I understand this &quot;Boggle&quot; is the second coming, but I don't have it yet. Somehow I'll manage. <br>
<br>
I DO have Rapture now, thanks to the excellent suggestions and practices noted in this thread.  In the interest of learning new tactics and wanting a clever pull message of my own, I tried this.<br>
<br>
Rapture says it's un(ir?)resistable &lt;61. Dorking around the PoV GY, I can attest to: yes it lands, but it may slide off just as quick. With a mage pulling (and 2 tanks chomping at the bit), getting them mezzed was easy. Getting tash, slow, cripple, and then the mind wipe off was very difficult. I had 3 seconds to seemed less than 42 seconds.  Even when I got them all cast, the mind wipe didn't seem to &quot;take&quot; anyway. Considering I generated more aggro in 30 seconds than I usually do in a whole fight (and get aggro), I'm not surprised. Unless I'm really missing something? I would have surely died if not for the Shadow Knight in group, very eager to take the rights to the mob back. &quot;Enchanter is going to do WHAT?&quot;<br>
<br>
I wasn't able to pull because I ran out of mana trying to keep up with everything. I noticed the original poster was 65 (VoQ) and FT 15, how nice for him. I do not have these advantages in spite of +mana items and mana tapping be specialty of mine. Haste is just a killer, with little relief in site. I still need to be able to sit between pulls, pony isn't quick enough to pull with.<br>
<br>
So, that's the next chapter of my story. I survived to near 60 and have new games to play. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1F0000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sunmina>Sunmina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Giant Squishies in Rathe</span><br>  Posts: 237<br> <font color=#AAAAAA>(9/5/03 12:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Aggro Management/was: when do you slow?</span><hr size=1> I was pulling at level 60 and without all this gear, so it's not just about gear.  I realize my comments are usually sarcastic but that's me.<br>
<br>
Rapture is a nice spell and is indeed unresistable.  It also has a fixed duration.  However, it has a long recast and is not really meant for exp situations.  It requires a lot of mana and doesn't last very long.  It also has a level cap of 60 in terms of mobs it can affect so you're not going to be able to use it in most tier 2 exp areas.  In other words, if you're under level 60 you really shouldn't be in PoV.  Not until you can get apathy, sleep and bliss.<br>
<br>
For other zones, you can do this with GoK or even with Dazzle depending on the zone.  I originally did it with Dazzle and GoK in Sebilis and Velks pulling village, juggs and so on.  This is about 3 years ago and pre FE so please, no gear rants.<br>
<br>
Second, if you're saying your gear sucks then fix it.  I would say the same thing to a warrior who had crap for gear.  There's plenty of options these days.  Get a mana preservation item if you don't have one yet.  Get more FT.  It's not that hard.  The nice thing about the last 2 years is that they actually made gear important for casters.  So get some.<br>
<br>
Haste is a killer, so get your epic.  Mana is an issue, so get FT and mana preservation.  Time is an issue so get spell haste.  All of these items are available and not that rare.  If you don't have the proper gear for your level, then that's your issue, not mine.  Post a magelo if you want and I can point out some items you may want to look for.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry, my sympathy for people who like to blame their gear for their issues is about zero. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><br>
