<br>
The problem with using a pet is you have to be really tight about the agro you gain... not too much... not too little. You really learn quick how good your tank is. Also keep in mind that different types of mobs gain agro at a different rate from certain spells than other mobs; even in the same zone. Learn the agro rates of the mobs in the zone you're hunting in. Is it tash that's ticking them off, or slow? It usually takes me about 6 to 10 pulls to really get the feel of a mob I've never hunted before. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub75.ezboard.com/btheshoemakers"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.pwshift.com/tr/images/sigs/nekkid.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
