<br>
She is right about redusing agro by pulling.......<br>
<br>
She is right about MA's not gaining proper agro will get you agroed.<br>
<br>
You don't have to go oom pulling. When you are out of mana it is because you do too much. &quot;But I have too......&quot;<br>
<br>
Look at your &quot;but I have too&quot; list and trim it. <br>
<br>
When you pull you have the ability to single pull in most cases. Choose a good camp with no roamers walking up on you, and you save the mana used to hold a mob during the fight. <br>
Choose a camp with both caster and melee mobs and use your drains.<br>
Do NOT try to carry the group..... If tank dont hold agro like he should, if his hp drops like a rock, if dps is low, then you are not the remedy. <br>
If you have no mana to DD, don't. The damage you primarily do is indirect.<br>
You primary damage comes from mana regen and haste.<br>
Do not worry that you are not usefull, that you do not help the group kill faster.<br>
Every slow that lands saves healer mana and so do every mezz......<br>
<br>
If your group don't see that, they need to upgrade the gear between their ears. You are no healer, you are no nuker. You can crowd control and that is what you do.<br>
<br>
Sure, you will hear tales about enchanters saving the day and adding awesome dps with charmed and hasted pets..... Try it, if it takes too much of healers mana, stop.<br>
<br>
This is where Sunmina is dead wrong....<br>
You can not be her. You have to find your own way to play your class. This will not make you a bad chanter by default.... But unless you master all aspects of the class you will never be a great one. I play a so-so okay chanter. Sadly that goes a long way on Morell-Thule.<br>
<br>
I rarely get to pull these days. That stopped in my forties when i started to group with a great paladin. He was very protective as well. When you can tash on inc and slow right away... well, I don't argue <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
I just enjoy. I had the pleasure of his compagny to my higher mid 50'es..<br>
<br>
Thank you Nesodo.<br>
<br>
Many pickup groups are afraid to let the chanter pull... and I do to some extend atract protective tanks. Not because I am particulary feminim, but because I let them. <br>
You can have a hard time getting permission to pull.<br>
<br>
If you want to pull.. use your friends list. Your friendslist is one of your best assests. Put the people you like grouping with on it.<br>
<br>
Enjoy what you do, and don't be scared if tank gets hurt a little. Tanks are ment to get hurt. Just don't let him die... you have that long wait on rezz, buffs, oom healers and oh... you are likely to gain agro if he dies. Remember that the tanks are made to take the blows aimed at you. Most of them are fiercely proud of their ability to do so.<br>
<br>
Stop attacking Sunmina for what she say... Her advice works for her. <br>
<br>
DO attack her for being so blunt if it bothers you. <br>
<br>
Take her up on her offer to help you with finding good gear. She have seen alot of what is out there. Her post shows that she have a keen eye for where you can go hunting and this is just too great a resource to pass it by. So, let her know what you have and let her help you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#0E0E0E><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rdreina>RdReina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#AAAAAA>(9/8/03 10:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Aggro Management/was: when do you slow?</span><hr size=1> I appreciate the advice, as I indicated in my comments. I apologize for the gender mix-up. I did not intend it as a disrespect. I've got no doubt to her credibility. One doesn't live to 65 by being passive, or spend three years building a character you don't adore. I can and do appreciate the wisdom that comes with this time spent.<br>
