<br>
Alot of my ideas come from talking to two 65 cleric mates of mine, and is focused on HP Loss reduction around the Pulls. I like to get the slow on quickly to reduce overall HP loss for group.  Runes/DS are important part here.  <br>
<br>
Now for WHEN to slow..IMHO there are a few options depending upon whether Tash line is required.  Tash is bad agro, and a slow on top is just asking for it.  This often leaves you slowing mobs at 60-80% hp to avoid agro from rapid casting.  I try the following each time: Try at least two slow without a tash on mob.  If it sticks - woot, if not well tash, then slow.  Try a second, and third..usually buy now you will know if it was just a one off resist.  Avoiding Tash to slow saves much agro..but you still need to Tash for the other casters.  Avoid Tash first up if you can.<br>
<br>
Pulling with Slow - This is a favourite of mine: 1. You get to find out fast if your spell resists. 2. If it sticks- you get agro for pet. 3. Just take it like a man/woman .  The tanks will get the agro pretty quicky if your not agroing.  This method works best with a PALLY (My personal Gods) who can stun.  At level 65 I use a Arcane Rune buff to pull as this will take all the dmg until the MA gets it. 4. Use Pacify line to reduce adds.  This is the most UNDERUSED chanter spell from what i can gather from grouping.  Some of the nerfing that people said was around I didnt discover.  ToV for example, I was told no way would it work...it does.  This will allow you to pull rooms/dungeons what ever- you can even pacify to the named then pull for your group.<br>
<br>
I always have a pet up- and have him hasted with weapons.  The added DPS is noticable over time.<br>
<br>
OKAY- Just read over previous and will add following affirmations from above posts:  RUNES are your friend. Use Rune3 until you get Rune 5 if plat a prob.  <br>
AC is important to consider when upgrading.  Memblur i only use ever on mezzez, and only then if multiple mobs- otherwise ive tashed/slowed/crippled/mana tapped that mf b4 hes even woken.  He gonna be real cranky but you want the agro for your pet.  <br>
+60 I agree, if the MA cannot get the agro off you within about 5 secs, your in trouble.  AR holds up to most initial melee from mobs plus a little (usually 4x250s then whats left)-recast if you have mana.  <br>
Dont OOM yourself slowing. Let others know your low, and if you need to med thru-make sure you give your healer notice.  Remember BARDS, NECRO, SHAM , RAN (proc) can all slow to some degree, Its not always up to you.  I use a necro to slow undead in groups, 60% slow for nearly 1/2 mana cost us, when i need the med.<br>
<br>
Everyone has their own style, and i still enjoy getting hit.  Im crazy but then again..you had better Emredrum Beforeyoudie)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Master Emredrum Beforeyoudie<br>
Coercer of MT<br>
